[Name] Mono
[Summary] An open source development platform based on the .NET
framework
[License] Compiler & tools: GNU General Public License; runtime libraries: GNU Library GPL 2.0; class libraries: MIT X11
[Description]
Mono is the open source development platform based on the .NET
framework. It allows developers to build Linux and cross-platform
applications with improved developer productivity. Mono's .NET
implementation is based on the ECMA standards for C# and the Common
Language Infrastructure. You'll need the optional libgdiplus package 
if you want to do graphics.
[Homepage] http://www.go-mono.com/